The paper discusses object detection for mobile robots, specifically unmanned ground vehicles, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed method uses a camera for object detection, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of learning and trust factors, which are common in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the use of sensors for location estimation, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
